  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dae\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dba \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Speaker seeks support from all parties",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena said today that he expects the support of all parties to successfully conclude the election to be held tomorrow (20) in accordance with the relevant rules and to respect democracy.",
        "He mentioned this in the Parliamentary Affairs Committee held this morning (19). The speaker also said that he appreciates the support of all parties to successfully conduct this process of selecting the successor president within the relevant legal framework.",
        "Mr. Dhammika Dasanayake, the Secretary General of the Parliament, who is the Returning Officer of the secret poll held tomorrow, said that before the polling, all the necessary guidelines will be informed to the honorable members according to the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981.",
        "Meanwhile, it was decided that the Parliament will meet again on the 27th in the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs held today. It was decided to present the emergency proclamation announced by the Acting President under the Public Security Act for approval on that day."
      ],
